Description: This package implements interrupted time series analysis for both continuous and count outcomes, and quantifies the associated effect size. It has been extended to support multiple disruption events, zero-inflated count models, seasonal adjustments via Fourier terms, and mixed-effects architectures. The main functions fit an ITS regression model, and then use the fitted values and the model-based counterfactual values to quantify the effect size (Cohen's d via parametric bootstrapping for continuous outcomes, and relative risk for count outcomes).
